  "grammar": [
    {
      "p": "莫过于",
      "e": "A formal superlative: 'nothing surpasses…; the greatest/most typical is none other than…'. Often follows 最…的 to crown one example above all others. 例：人生最大的幸福莫过于家人平安。",
      "x": "最典型的莫过于年龄与死亡。 — The most typical cases are none other than age and death."
    },
    {
      "p": "之所以…，是因为…",
      "e": "Result first, cause second: 'the reason why A is that B'. Putting the phenomenon up front makes the explanation land with more force. 例：他之所以成功，是因为从不放弃。",
      "x": "委婉语之所以如此发达，是因为汉文化高度重视面子。 — The reason euphemism is so highly developed is that Chinese culture places enormous weight on face."
    },
    {
      "p": "固然…，但…",
      "e": "A concessive pivot: 'admittedly A, but B'. It grants the first point genuine validity before asserting that the second matters more. 例：钱固然重要，但健康更重要。",
      "x": "听懂委婉语固然重要，但更重要的是学会使用它。 — Understanding euphemisms is admittedly important, but more important still is learning to use them."
